<div id="review_433011490" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/433011490" />
    <a title="Cassandra Giovanni" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9812798-cassandra-giovanni"><img alt="Cassandra Giovanni" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442630584p2/9812798.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/433011490?book_show_action=true">Oct 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cassandra Giovanni" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cassandra Giovanni" href="/user/show/9812798-cassandra-giovanni">Cassandra Giovanni</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9812798-cassandra-giovanni?shelf=indie">indie</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer433011490" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2368021369145999313">3.5 Stars<br/>Where to begin? Honestly, I did not believe that I would finish the book. The writing is great first off, but it&apos;s very technical. For me this caused the dialogue to feel choppy. The description was very intricate and detailed down to every piece of food the characters consumed. This was a bit much for me, and I found myself skimming many parts. The reason I didn&apos;t feel I would finish was because of the slow start and high levels of description. The storyline is great, and I really enjo</span>
  <span id="freeText2368021369145999313" style="display:none">3.5 Stars<br />Where to begin? Honestly, I did not believe that I would finish the book. The writing is great first off, but it's very technical. For me this caused the dialogue to feel choppy. The description was very intricate and detailed down to every piece of food the characters consumed. This was a bit much for me, and I found myself skimming many parts. The reason I didn't feel I would finish was because of the slow start and high levels of description. The storyline is great, and I really enjoyed the ending. As I got deeper into the book I was able to become accustomed to the flow and detail level, but I also noticed that the character's maturity didn't match their ages-- especially once they reached Mere. One thing that struck me was the third POV, why? I normally hate it and here I didn't. It flowed well in this form and allowed for two stories to be made into one. I loved the budding romance between Megan and Zachi. At first when I started feeling it, it was creepy. However, as you grow to see that he was her guardian, you understand. I'm also hoping that Chloe and Preston can be together, although their insta-love was a bit unrealistic to me. I can understand the instant attraction, but saying "deeply in love" after what accumulates to a few hours? The title is very fitting-- the story is enchanting, and the ending made it so I know I will come back for more. This is more middle grade than young adult, and I can see a young boy really enjoying this.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2368021369145999313" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


