      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laurie Franco" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laurie Franco" href="/user/show/12063005-laurie-franco">Laurie Franco</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer406446323" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9508987366316422272">Thoroughly enjoyable book. It did take me a few chapters to really get into it, since the beginning was a bit...less interesting(?) than the rest of the book. Once into it however, I had a hard time putting it down. I liked the whole storyline, and thought it was cool the way the &quot;siblings&quot; turned out to be guardians. I&apos;m REALLY hoping that Chloe turns out to be Lillie, but as is the case with almost all of the books I&apos;ve been reading lately, it&apos;s a darn series!! And it just left me HANGING! I&apos;m</span>
  <span id="freeText9508987366316422272" style="display:none">Thoroughly enjoyable book. It did take me a few chapters to really get into it, since the beginning was a bit...less interesting(?) than the rest of the book. Once into it however, I had a hard time putting it down. I liked the whole storyline, and thought it was cool the way the "siblings" turned out to be guardians. I'm REALLY hoping that Chloe turns out to be Lillie, but as is the case with almost all of the books I've been reading lately, it's a darn series!! And it just left me HANGING! I'm dying to know what will happen next, and even though I haven't read it yet, I will be willing to go out on a limb and recommend the entire series, however many books it might be, since Mere Enchantment was excellent and I would expect nothing less as Ms. Rivoli's story progresses! Great job, and keep up the good work!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9508987366316422272" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


