<div id="review_335104921" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/335104921" />
    <a title="Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3368925-kelly"><img alt="Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1387470655p2/3368925.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/335104921?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly" href="/user/show/3368925-kelly">Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3368925-kelly?shelf=reviewed-on-my-blog">reviewed-on-my-blog</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3368925-kelly?shelf=ya-fantasy">ya-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3368925-kelly?shelf=what-a-waste-of-space">what-a-waste-of-space</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer335104921" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8269354349695500774"><a href='www.readinhouston.blogspot.com' rel='nofollow noopener'>
  <img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380364129i/715688._SX540_.png' width='600' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/>
</a><br/><br/>Despite what anyone may think, I absolutely hate to give a bad review. I feel sorry for the author and anyone else involved with the book. Because lets face it, it isn&apos;t just the Author who pored their sole and time into this project, a husband/wife may have had to read it several times, a neighbor may have given an idea or two...<br/><br/>That being said, <b>WTF happened to the end?</b> Did I just not get the last couple of chapters in my e-copy? it&apos;s like Rivoli got tied up with something else and when she</span>
  <span id="freeText8269354349695500774" style="display:none"><a href="www.readinhouston.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380364129i/715688._SX540_.png" width="600" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a><br><br>Despite what anyone may think, I absolutely hate to give a bad review. I feel sorry for the author and anyone else involved with the book. Because lets face it, it isn't just the Author who pored their sole and time into this project, a husband/wife may have had to read it several times, a neighbor may have given an idea or two...<br><br>That being said, <b>WTF happened to the end?</b> Did I just not get the last couple of chapters in my e-copy? it's like Rivoli got tied up with something else and when she came back to the MS, hit send with out adding the conclusion. I had to stop and re-read the last few pages because I though maybe I skipped five or six pages.<br><br>This novel did have an intriguing idea and world, and I think if Rivoli decides to go back and edit this novel, she should expand on the world and finish the ending. <br><br>I won't go into any of my other issues with this, you'll just have to read my <a href="http://readinhouston.blogspot.com/2012/08/mere-enchantment.html" rel="nofollow noopener">blog</a> if you want to hear more.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8269354349695500774" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
